title: Model switch has no safety net — bad selection bricks session
---
When changing the model (via models set tool or models set-default CLI), there is no validation beyond catalog lookup. If the selected model is unreachable, misconfigured, or incompatible, the session becomes unusable because every subsequent LLM call fails.

Current behaviour:
1. set_model checks Models_catalog.find_by_full_name — if found, immediately sets it
2. set-default normalizes the name and writes to config — no connectivity test
3. Neither path prints a rollback command
4. Neither path sends a test prompt to verify the model actually works
5. If the model is bad, the user is stuck — they cannot even ask the agent to switch back

Desired behaviour:
1. Before switching, print the rollback command (models set <previous_model> or clawq models set-default <previous_model>)
2. Validate early: check provider is configured, API key exists, model name is recognized
3. Send a lightweight test prompt (e.g. Respond with OK) to the new model with a short timeout
4. Only commit the switch if the test succeeds
5. If test fails, report the error and keep the current model
6. For session-scoped changes via the tool: include the rollback command in the response so the agent can self-recover

Acceptance criteria:
- models set prints rollback command before switching
- models set-default prints rollback command before switching
- Both paths attempt a minimal test completion against the target model
- If test fails, the switch is aborted with a clear error message
- Previous model remains active after a failed switch
- Session agent receives rollback instructions in the tool response